.TH KIRO-PROBE 8 "2026-05-19" "Kiro" "Kiro System Tools"
.SH NAME
kiro-probe \- upload a hardware probe to linux-hardware.org
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B kiro-probe
[\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR]
[\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR]
[\fB\-d\fR|\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR]
[\fB\-s\fR|\fB\-\-save\fR [\fIDIR\fR]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B kiro-probe
installs
.B hw-probe
if it is not already present, then runs
.B hw-probe\ \-all\ \-upload
to collect a full hardware inventory and upload it to
.IR https://linux-hardware.org .
.PP
The upload generates a unique probe URL that can be shared for hardware
compatibility reports and bug reports.
.PP
With
.BR \-\-save ,
the probe is instead saved locally (an
.I hw.info
directory plus an
.I hw.info.txz
archive) and a readable HTML insight report is generated from it via
.BR kiro-probe-report (8).
This is the offline path: no server contact, no upload.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print a help message and exit.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Print version information and exit.
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-dry\-run
Show what would be executed without making any changes.
.TP
.BR \-s ", " "\-\-save " [\fIDIR\fR]
Save the probe locally to
.I DIR
(default: current directory) instead of uploading, then generate an HTML
insight report from it with
.BR kiro-probe-report (8).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/bin/hw-probe
Probe binary installed by the hw-probe package.
.TP
.I /usr/local/lib/kiro-common.sh
Shared library.
.SH EXAMPLES
.EX
kiro-probe --dry-run
kiro-probe
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR kiro-probe-report (8),
.BR hw-probe (1),
.BR pacman (8)
.SH AUTHOR
Erik Dubois <https://www.erikdubois.be>
